		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">The Language Instinct</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><i><b>The Language Instinct</b></i> is a book by <a href="/wiki/Steven_Pinker" title="Steven Pinker">Steven Pinker</a> for a general audience, published in 1994. In it, Pinker argues that <a href="/wiki/Human" title="Human">humans</a> are born with an innate capacity for <a href="/wiki/Language" title="Language">language</a>. In addition, he deals sympathetically with <a href="/wiki/Noam_Chomsky" title="Noam Chomsky">Noam Chomsky</a>'s claim that all human language shows evidence of a <a href="/wiki/Universal_grammar" title="Universal grammar">universal grammar</a>. In the final chapter Pinker dissents from the skepticism shown by Chomsky that <a href="/wiki/Evolution" title="Evolution">evolution</a> by <a href="/wiki/Natural_selection" title="Natural selection">natural selection</a> is up to par with the challenge of explaining a human language instinct.</p>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Surfacegyri.JPG" class="image" title="Some of the areas of the brain involved in language processing: Broca's area, Wernicke's area, Supramarginal gyrus, Angular gyrus, Primary Auditory Cortex"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/86/Surfacegyri.JPG/300px-Surfacegyri.JPG" width="300" height="270" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Surfacegyri.JPG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Some of the areas of the brain involved in language processing: <a href="/wiki/Broca%27s_area" title="Broca's area">Broca's area</a>, <a href="/wiki/Wernicke%27s_area" title="Wernicke's area">Wernicke's area</a>, <a href="/wiki/Supramarginal_gyrus" title="Supramarginal gyrus" class="mw-redirect">Supramarginal gyrus</a>, <a href="/wiki/Angular_gyrus" title="Angular gyrus">Angular gyrus</a>, <a href="/wiki/Primary_Auditory_Cortex" title="Primary Auditory Cortex" class="mw-redirect">Primary Auditory Cortex</a></div>
</div>
</div>
